  "content": "# Devcontainer Docker Build Verification (2026-03-26)\n\n## Build Results\n- **Image**: `corvia-devc-test` built from `.devcontainer/Dockerfile`\n- **Base**: `rust:1.88-trixie`\n- **Build time**: 14m 1s\n- **Image size**: 20.9 GB\n- **Outcome**: All 27 steps passed\n\n## Issues Found\n\n### 1. GID collision: vscode user primary group is `render` (GID 1000)\n- `groupadd -f render` claims GID 1000 before user creation\n- `vscode` user inherits `render` as primary group instead of own group\n- Impact: Low (remoteUser is root), but breaks if switched to vscode user\n- Fix: Move user creation before GPU group creation in Dockerfile\n- Tracked: https://github.com/chunzhe10/corvia-workspace/issues/15\n\n### 2. Image size (20.9 GB) — optimization opportunities\n- CUDA pip packages: ~5 GB (biggest target)\n- Playwright browsers: ~4 GB (duplicate copy + install)\n- Ollama: ~1 GB (could be optional service)\n- Cache cleanup missing after pip/npm installs\n- Tracked: https://github.com/chunzhe10/corvia-workspace/issues/16\n\n## All Verified Components\n- Core: rustc 1.88.0, cargo, node v20.19.2, python3 3.13.5, uv 0.11.1\n- Tools: gh 2.88.1, cmake 3.31.6, task 3.49.1, claude 2.1.84, ollama, vsce 3.7.1\n- GPU: CUDA cublas/cudart .so.12, OpenVINO 2025.3.0, Chrome 146\n- Scripts: lib.sh, post-create.sh, post-start.sh, setup_wrapper.py, Taskfile.yml — all parse clean\n",
